        <div id="british-columbia-victoria-attractions" class="tabcontent">
            <div class="tabcontent-text-container">
                <p>Victoria is known for its beautiful historic structures, including the magnificent BC Parliament Building and chateau-like Fairmont Express. The city also hosts the Royal BC Museum and the picturesque Fisherman's Wharf, which consists of several floating piers lined with shops, restaurants, and colorful floating homes.</p>
                <p>On the western outskirts of the city is the stunning 20th century Hatley Castle, which was once owned by the British Royal Family.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
